As the crisis in Mozambique deepens, aid organisations are calling for urgent and decisive action from continental leadership. A SADC troika summit that was due to take place in Maputo tomorrow, has been postponed to Thursday. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Southern African Development Community will convene an Extraordinary Double Troika Summit on Thursday, 8 April 2021. READ: SADC to meet over Mozambique unrest The summit will focus on measures to deal with the attacks in Mozambique. The attacks have left more than 8,000 people displaced. Mozambique has seen continued terrorist attacks in Cabo Delgado over the past few weeks, leaving many people dead or injured. President Keabetswe Masisi from Botswana says Mozambican terrorism is an affront to peace and affects the international community as a whole.